<p>The TAFISA Certified Leadership Courses in Sport for All were developed to train and qualify national Sport for All leaders around the globe. </p><p>Since their inception in 2007 and 2011 respectively, more than 30 International and National TAFISA CLCs have been successfully held all across the world, from Iran to Trinidad & Tobago, from Kazakhstan to Australia, from China to Tanzania, from Argentina to Latvia and beyond.  With the support of the IOC for the development of the TAFISA CLCs from 2010, TAFISA has seen an encouraging rise in NOC hosts and participants alongside TAFISA member organizations.</p><p>The next International CLC to be held in Kuala Lumpur, Malaysia between 4-10 May 2014 at IYC - International Youth Centre, Cheras, Kuala Lumpur.</p><p><b>Download documents:</b></p><p><a href="http://www.asfaa.org/pdf/Malaysia CLC Brochure 2014.docx">Brochure </a>| <a href="pdf/Malaysia CLC Invitation Ltr 2014.docx">Invitation </a>| <a href="pdf/Malaysia CLC Registration Form 2014.docx">Registration</a></p><p>learn more <a href="http://www.tafisa.net/index.php?option=com_content&view=article&id=72&Itemid=75">here</a></p><p></p><p></p>